#Z = hac.linkage(dfr.head(100).T.loc['measurement'].dropna(axis=1), method='single', metric='correlation')

# Plot dendogram

plt.title('Hierarchical Clustering Dendrogram - single correlation - top 100 entries')
plt.xlabel('sample index')
plt.ylabel('distance')
hac.dendrogram(
    Z,
    leaf_rotation=90.,  # rotates the x axis labels
    leaf_font_size=8.,  # font size for the x axis labels
)
plt.show()

x=dfg.replace(100,np.nan).dropna()[:]

import scipy.cluster.hierarchy as hac
Z = hac.linkage(x, method='single', metric='correlation')

# Plot dendogram
plt.figure(figsize=(25, 10))
plt.title('Hierarchical Clustering Dendrogram - single correlation')
plt.xlabel('sample index')
plt.ylabel('distance')
hac.dendrogram(
    Z,
    leaf_rotation=90.,  # rotates the x axis labels
    leaf_font_size=8.,  # font size for the x axis labels
)
ax=plt.gca()
labels=[x.index[int(i.get_text())] for i in ax.get_xticklabels()]
labels=[meta.set_index('monitor_id').loc[x.index[int(i.get_text())]]['Original Point label:'] for i in ax.get_xticklabels()]
ax.set_xticklabels(labels,fontsize=15)
plt.show()

In [76]:
y = x.values #returns a numpy array
min_max_scaler = preprocessing.MinMaxScaler()
y_scaled = min_max_scaler.fit_transform(y)
w = pd.DataFrame(y_scaled,index=x.index)

Z = hac.linkage(w, method='complete', metric='canberra')

# Plot dendogram
plt.figure(figsize=(25, 10))
plt.title('Hierarchical Clustering Dendrogram - normalized canberra complete')
plt.xlabel('sample index')
plt.ylabel('distance')
hac.dendrogram(
    Z,
    leaf_rotation=90.,  # rotates the x axis labels
    leaf_font_size=8.,  # font size for the x axis labels
)
ax=plt.gca()
labels=[x.index[int(i.get_text())] for i in ax.get_xticklabels()]
labels=[meta.set_index('monitor_id').loc[x.index[int(i.get_text())]]['Original Point label:'] for i in ax.get_xticklabels()]
ax.set_xticklabels(labels,fontsize=15)
plt.show()


def print_clusters(timeSeries, Z, k, plot=False):
    # k Number of clusters I'd like to extract
    results = fcluster(Z, k, criterion='maxclust')
    
    # check the results
    s = pd.Series(results)
    clusters = s.unique()

    for c in clusters:
        cluster_indeces = s[s==c].index
        print("Cluster %d number of entries %d" % (c, len(cluster_indeces)))
        if plot:
            timeSeries.T.iloc[:,cluster_indeces].rolling(200).mean().plot()
            plt.show()

print_clusters(x, Z, 6, plot=True)

def print_clusters(timeSeries, Z, k, plot=False):
    # k Number of clusters I'd like to extract
    results = fcluster(Z, k, criterion='maxclust')
    
    # check the results
    s = pd.Series(results)
    clusters = s.unique()

    for c in clusters:
        cluster_indeces = s[s==c].index
        print("Cluster %d number of entries %d" % (c, len(cluster_indeces)))
        if plot:
            timeSeries.T.iloc[:,cluster_indeces].rolling(400).mean().plot()
            plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.1, 1.05))
            plt.show()

def print_clusters(timeSeries, Z, k, plot=False):
    # k Number of clusters I'd like to extract
    results = fcluster(Z, k, criterion='distance')
    
    # check the results
    s = pd.Series(results)
    clusters = s.unique()

    for c in clusters:
        cluster_indeces = s[s==c].index
        print("Cluster %d number of entries %d" % (c, len(cluster_indeces)))
        if plot:
            timeSeries.T.iloc[:,cluster_indeces].rolling(400).mean().plot()
            plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.1, 1.05))
            plt.show()

#print_clusters(meta[['monitor_id','Original Point label:']].join(x,on='monitor_id').set_index('Original Point label:').drop('monitor_id',axis=1), Z, 8, plot=True)
print_clusters(x, Z, 0.75, plot=True)
